<h2>The SWAMI RULES</h2>

<h3 class="bg-primary">Object</h3>
<p>
    It's simple. Each player starts the season with a mythical $1000. The player
    with the most moola after the bowl games is deemed the 'Swami'. This year, the
    season will start September 2nd, and run every week there are a full slate of
    games through “bowl week”.
</p>

<br />
<h3 class="bg-primary">Rules</h3>
<p>
    Every Tuesday morning, 16 games will be chosen from an online site (ESPN’s Daily
    line from the Mirage). The games and the 'opening lines' will be sent via email
    to all the players. These lines are subject to change, due to injuries and the
    like. On Thursday, final lines will be distributed. These are the official lines
    used to place your bets. All bets for the week must be in by 12pm EST on Friday.
    Occasionally there is a worthwhile Thursday night game. If it is a selected game
    and you choose to bet on it, ALL your bets for the week must be in by Thursday 4pm.
    Here's a sample of what you'd receive:
</p>

