<p>
    You would send me an email with the team name that you think will cover and the
    dollar amount you would like to wager. In the above example, I would send an email
    that said Bama $500, and Northwood $500. I would be betting $1000 for the week,
    picking Alabama to beat Auburn by more than 27 points and Northwood to win or not
    lose by more than 5 points. If a game is listed as 'NL' (no line) on Thursday, you
    cannot bet on the game. Example: Florida State decides to kick a QB off the team
    for stealing crablegs, more than likely, the line will go to NL.. A line of 'even'
    translates into “pick the winner”.
</p>

<br />
<p>
    You can bet on as many/few games as you like. All bets must be in multiples of $10.
    <span style="font-weight:900;  text-decoration:underline;">
        If you have positive earnings going into the week, your minimum bet is 1/2 of your
        current monies.
    </span>
    Example: At the start of the season, we all begin the first week
    with $1000. We all must bet at least $500 that week. This ensures that someone doesn't
    take a gamble the first few weeks and then decides to sit on his/her earnings.
</p>

<br />
<p>
    <span style="font-weight:900;  text-decoration:underline;">
        If you go in the hole >= $1000, You’re OUT
    </span>
