    </span>
</p>

<br />
<p>
    <span style="font-weight:900;  text-decoration:underline;">
        If you fail to turn in your bets, that week your minimum bid will be placed on the Favorite
        with the largest line.
    </span>
    Example: Marc decides to get married over a football weekend (not very smart) and does not 
    turn in his wagers. He currently has $2000. From the above table, he would automatically 
    have a $1000 bet on Alabama (he's a lucky guy). You can turn in your bets anytime after you
    receive the first email on Tuesday.
    <span style="font-weight:900;  text-decoration:underline;">
        Once they are in, you cannot change them.
    </span>
    Remember    that these lines could change between Tuesday and Thursday, so if you turn in a 
    bet of $500 on Tuesday and the line changes, you’re stuck with the new line (can move in 
    your favor too). If the line moves to NL, the bet is cancelled.
</p>

